The listing comes on the back of the entertainment firm having enrolled for the NSE incubation programme dubbled Ibuka.The programme has attracted 27 firms since launch two years ago. The Rabar family has revealed its Sh294.5 million fortune in Homeboyz Entertainment (HBE) as they defied Covid-19 headwinds to list the company on the Nairobi bourse yesterday.
The listing statement puts each share of the company at Sh4.66 with the former DJ-turned entertainment and events organiser Myke Rabar holding 35.612 million shares worth Sh165.95 million.



